name: Diethyl 3,4-dimethylthieno[2,3-b]thiophene-2,5-dicarboxylate
source: Karthikeyan M.; Glen R.C.; Bender A. General melting point prediction based on a diverse compound dataset and artificial neural networks. J. Chem. Inf. Model.; 2005; 45(3); 581-3904
Reason: 3,4-dimethylthieno[2,3-b]thiophene-2,5-dicarboxylate has a melting point that we can compare to by analyzing its structural components. Starting with the basic unit of thieno[2,3-b]thiophene, which has a melting point around 106°C. The methyl groups (three in total) add approximately +10°C due to increased molecular weight and rigidity. The dimethylthiophene moiety introduces additional rigidity and potential hydrogen bonding, estimated at around +20°C. The carboxylate group can participate in hydrogen bonding, raising the melting point by approximately +10°C. The presence of two additional phenyl groups can significantly augment the melting point due to the increase in molecular weight and pi-pi interactions, estimated at around +40°C each.
